==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Negation
<hw>Ne*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>negatio</ets>, fr. <ets>negare</ets> to say no, to deny;
<ets>ne</ets> not + the root of <ets>aio</ets> I say; cf. Gr. <?/, Skr.
<ets>ah</ets> to say; cf. F. <ets>n⟦eacute⟧gation</ets>. See
<er>No</er>, <pos>adv.</pos>, and cf. <er>Adage</er>, <er>Deny</er>,
<er>Renegade</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of denying; assertion
of the nonreality or untruthfulness of anything; declaration that
something is not, or has not been, or will not be; denial; -- the
opposite of <ant>affirmation</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our assertions and <qex>negations</qex> should be yea and nay.</q>
<rj><qau>Rogers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>Description or definition by
denial, exclusion, or exception; statement of what a thing is not, or
has not, from which may be inferred what it is or has.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Negative</ent>⟦br⟧
